    "bodyHtml": "<p>Heading: Agentic AI 101\nSubheadings to create TOC:</p>\n<p>What “agentic” means</p>\n<p>Agentic AI is a pattern where the model doesn’t just answer once. It can plan steps, call tools, and iterate until it completes a goal.</p>\n<p>Where agents help (and where they don’t)</p>\n<p>Agents shine when work involves multiple steps: searching, transforming, checking, and producing a final output.\nThey struggle when the task is unclear, the tools are unreliable, or there is no way to verify correctness.</p>\n<p>The reliability checklist</p>\n<p>Use clear goal + constraints</p>\n<p>Break work into small steps</p>\n<p>Add tool-result validation</p>\n<p>Use timeouts and limits</p>\n<p>Log what the agent did</p>\n<p>A simple example workflow</p>\n<p>Read requirement</p>\n<p>Draft output</p>\n<p>Verify against checklist</p>\n<p>Finalize and format</p>\n<p>Key takeaway</p>\n<p>Agentic AI works best when you treat it like an automation pipeline with guardrails—not magic.</p>\n",
