    "bodyHtml": "<p>The core idea</p>\n<p>Editors work in a CMS. Hugo fetches published content at build time and generates static pages.</p>\n<p>Why it’s fast and stable</p>\n<p>No server rendering on each request</p>\n<p>Pages are static and cached</p>\n<p>Simple hosting (Netlify)</p>\n<p>Trade-offs (honest)</p>\n<p>Content updates require a rebuild</p>\n<p>You must handle missing fields</p>\n<p>Preview needs extra setup (optional)</p>\n<p>The pipeline in plain English</p>\n<p>Sanity stores the content</p>\n<p>A script fetches posts/authors/categories</p>\n<p>Hugo templates render pages</p>\n<p>Netlify deploys</p>\n<p>Key takeaway</p>\n<p>Static + headless is a strong default when you want simplicity and speed.</p>\n",
