    "title": "Adding AI into a CMS Without Breaking Governance",
    "bodyHtml": "<p>Why CMS + AI needs guardrails</p>\n<p>AI can generate text fast, but content teams need consistency, legal safety, and brand voice.</p>\n<p>The minimal safe workflow</p>\n<p>AI generates a draft only (never auto-publish)</p>\n<p>Author reviews and edits</p>\n<p>Reviewer approves</p>\n<p>Publish triggers automation (cache purge etc.)</p>\n<p>What to log</p>\n<p>Prompt used</p>\n<p>Model/tool used</p>\n<p>Timestamp</p>\n<p>Author who requested</p>\n<p>What changed after human edit</p>\n<p>UI ideas that are easy to explain</p>\n<p>“Generate draft” button</p>\n<p>“Rewrite in brand tone” dropdown</p>\n<p>“Summarize this post” action</p>\n<p>Side panel showing AI output + diff</p>\n<p>Key takeaway</p>\n<p>If you can’t explain the workflow to a non-technical reviewer, it’s too complex.</p>\n",
